    "summary": "Dr. Marein van Schaaijk (born 1947 in The Netherlands) is the director of Micromacro Consultants. This bureau has executed macro model (including poverty module) building projects, in Cura\u00e7ao, Suriname, Poland, Indonesia, Kenya, Ethiopia, Aruba, Namibia, Macedonia and Zambia. Furthermore it does macro and micro economic research in The Netherlands. See www.micromacroconsultants.com\n\nHe is a specialist in macroeconomics, quantitative microeconomic analysis, economic model building, poverty analysis and national accounting. After his studies, he worked for three years in Surinam (South America) to train statisticians and to set up the Surinam National Accounts and other basic statistics. Afterwards he worked for 18 years for the Central Planning Bureau of the Netherlands in several research and management positions (regional planning, micro-economic analysis of household income, labor and housing market, energy and the national budget). \n\nIn 1994 he left government service to start Micromacro Consultants. Together with a small full time staff and a network of 23 highly experienced short term advisers, this bureau has performed micro and macroeconomic research for the Ministries of Housing, Health, Internal Affairs, Economics and Finance in the Netherlands and also for private organizations. The Bureau also successfully organized projects in model building and training in Cura\u00e7ao, Suriname, Poland, Indonesia, Kenya, Ethiopia, Aruba, Namibia, Macedonia and Zambia.\n\nDr. van Schaaijk holds a Ph.D. in macroeconomics from the University of Groningen (The Netherlands) and a Masters (cum laude) in economics from the University of Tilburg. He published many books and articles about economics and built Macroabc, a macro model including poverty module Micromacrosim, available as shareware on the internet: www.micromacroconsultants.com.",
